    "X 1∶T represent the observed time series data up to time T. The posterior probability of an extreme value occurring is given by P(E|X 1∶T) for the observed data.",
    "P(E) is the prior probability of an extreme event occurring, based on prior knowledge or historical data.",
    "P(X 1∶T |E) is the likelihood of observing the time series data X 1∶T given that an extreme event occurs.",
    "P(X 1∶T) is the evidence, which represents the total probability of observing the data X 1∶T, regardless of whether an extreme value occurs.",
